This paper proposes a dynamic MR imaging method using a multi-supervised network training technique to integrate both k-space and spatial prior knowledge. The method is based on deep learning and convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The paper also discusses the use of frequency domain information, which is related to signal processing (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for optimization, which is a common topic in neural engineering (cs.NE).
